{{Infobox television | show_name = Dr. Hala | image = | genre = Drama | creator = | developer = | writer = Claudia Marchalian<ref name="alakbar" /> | director = Ghaby Saad | creative_director = | starring = {{Plainlist| *Rita Barsona *[[Peter Semaan]] *[[Muhammad Ibrahim (actor)|Muhammad Ibrahim]] }} | opentheme = | endtheme = | country = Lebanon | language = Arabic | num_seasons = 1 | num_episodes = 30<ref name="alakbar" /> | producer = Marwan Haddad<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://elaph.com/Web/RadioTv/2009/1/398272.htm|title=ريتا برصونا وبيتر سمعان معاً من جديد في "دكتور هلا"|last=|first=|date=|website=elaph.com|publisher=|language=Arabic|trans-title=Rita Barsona and Peter Semaan together again in "Dr. Hala"|access-date=2016-09-03}}</ref> | runtime = <!-- Reliable source required --> | company = Marwa Group | network = [[MTV Lebanon]] | first_run = Lebanon | first_aired = {{Start date|2008|1|30}} | screenplay = | story = | website = mtv.com.lb/Programs/Drddot_Hala }}
'''Dr. Hala''' ({{Lang-ar|دكتور هلا}}) is a Lebanese television series produced in 2009 by Marwa Group. The series was written by Claudia Marchalian.<ref name="alakbar">{{Cite web|url=http://al-akhbar.com/node/92672|title="المستقبل": حبيبة قلبي "دكتور هلا"... والدراما اللبنانيّة|last=Basem|first=Al-Hakim|date=|website=|publisher=|trans-title=«Future»: My heart darling «Dr. Hala»... and the Lebanese drama|access-date=2016-09-02}}</ref>
==Plot== Hala (Rita Barsona) had bad emotional experiences in her youth. As an adult, she ignored love to focus on study and work, until she met the journalist Ghadi ([[Peter Semaan]]), with whom she fell in love. However, after a former lover Nadeem ([[Muhammad Ibrahim (actor)|Muhammad Ibrahim]]) returns, Hala lives in a struggle between the past, present and future.
