'''Jakub Auguston Jr.''' (born '''Giacomo Agustoni''' around 1668 - August 3, 1735, [[Plzeň]]) was an important [[baroque (architecture)|baroque]] architect in [[Plzeň]] and west [[Bohemia]]. His works include, tee [[Chotěšov Abbey]], the Church of Saint Anna and Saint Ruzena Limanska in Plzeň. He is buried in the church's crypt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zcu.cz/plzen/landm/anna-chr.html|title=Plzen, The Church of Saint Anna.|last=Wimmer|first=Milos|year=1998|publisher=University of Plzen|accessdate=2008-08-27}}</ref><ref>[http://www.khi.zcu.cz/Baroko.htm Tomáš Jílek, Viktor Viktora: Cultural and spiritual development of Western Bohemia in the Baroque period.]</ref>
