{{Infobox language |name=Kwangwa |nativename=Kwanga |states=[[Zambia]] |region= |speakers=2,400 Kwanga and Kwandi |date=2010 census |ref=<ref>{{e18|lyn|Luyana}}</ref> |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone K|Zone K]]) |fam6=[[Kavango languages|Kavango]]? |iso3=none |guthrie=K.37, K.721 |glotto=kwan1275 |glottoname=Kwanga |glotto2=kwan1274 |glottoname2=Kwandi }}
'''Kwangwa''' (Kwanga) is a [[Bantu language]] of Zambia.
Maho (2009) lists K.721 Kwandi as a distinct but closely related language.<ref name="Guthrie"/>
Kwandi and Kwanga had once been classified as dialects of the divergent [[Luyana language]].
