'''Muncești Highway''' ({{lang-ro|Şoseaua Muncești}}) is an urban highway located in the capital of [[Moldova]] - [[Chișinău]], in [[sectorul Botanica|Botanica sector]]. With a length of ca. 14 km it is the longest street of Chișinău; it starts from the border of Botanica and [[sectorul Centru|center of Chișinău]] - ''head to head'' with Gagarin Street, near to [[Chișinău Railway Station]], and ends at the city periphery with a [[viaduct]] near [[Sîngera]] town (which is also part of Chișinău Municipality), being continued to South-East of Moldova by M14 road (part of [[European route E58]] and [[European route E581]]). It goes in parallel with the Moldovan inter-urban railway route Chișinău–[[Bender, Moldova|Bender]], at a short distance from it. There are 970 [[House numbering|house (address) numbers]] on Munceşti Highway, and this is the host for a big number of industrial enterprises. This is one of the oldest streets of Chişinău. In the XVI–XVIII centuries in this area was located a homonymous village, Muncești, which later was enclosed in Chișinău.<ref>[http://www.jurnaltv.md/ro/news/2016/9/3/-quot-muncim-quot-pe-cea-mai-lunga-strada-din-capitala-10239542/ "Muncim" pe cea mai lungă stradă din capitală]. [[Jurnal TV]], 3 September 2016 {{ro icon}}</ref>

