'''Starsem''' is a European-Russian company that was created in 1996 to commercialise the [[Soyuz (rocket family)|Soyuz launcher]] internationally. Starsem is headquartered in [[Évry, Essonne|Évry]], France (near Paris) and has the following shareholders:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starsem.com/starsem/founding.htm |title=Founding companies |publisher=Starsem |access-date=25 October 2018}}</ref> * [[ArianeGroup]] (35%) * [[Arianespace]] (15%) * [[Roscosmos]] (25%) * [[TsSKB-Progress]] (25%)
